title: ICU Medical: 1Q Earnings Snapshot
text:
SAN CLEMENTE, Calif. (AP) _ ICU Medical Inc. (ICUI) on Wednesday reported first-quarter net income of $4.9 million.
The San Clemente, California-based company said it had profit of 23 cents per share. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs and restructuring costs, came to $2.26 per share.
The medical device maker posted revenue of $372 million in the period.
ICU Medical shares have increased 17 percent since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Wednesday, shares hit $253.05, a climb of 60 percent in the last 12 months.
